comment_data.body:
Pointers can only be compared if they are pointing within the same allocation. E.g.:

```c
char a[2];
char b[2];
if (&a[0] == &a[1]) ... // OK
if (&a[0] == &b[0]) ... // UB

// Similarly:
char a[2];
char *b = malloc(2);
if (&a[0] == b) ... // UB

// Or equally:
char *a = malloc(2);
char *b = malloc(2);
if (a == b) ... // UB
```

We can avoid the problem by doing:

```c
#define STRERROR_BUF_SIZE 256
char buf[STRERROR_BUF_SIZE];
const char *retstr = strerror_r(error, buf, sizeof(buf));

const size_t len = strlen(retstr);
assert(len < STRERROR_BUF_SIZE);  // can this happen? probably need a test to make sure it can't
char *str = (char *)malloc(len + 1);
if (str != nullptr) {
  memcpy(str, retstr, len + 1); // copy including null terminator
}
return str;
#undef STRERROR_BUF_SIZE
```

